12 (A) IN THIS SUBTITLE THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
13 INDICATED.
14 (B) (1) “AUTHORIZED REPAIR PROVIDER” MEANS A PERSON THAT IS
15 UNAFFILIATED WITH A MANUFACTURER AND, FOR THE PURPOSE OF OFFERING TO
16 PROVIDE SERVICES TO AN OWNER OF THE MANUFACTURER’S EQUIPMENT
17 REGARDING THE OWNER’S EQUIPMENT OR PART, HAS:
18 (I) AN ARRANGEMENT WITH THE MANUFACTURER UNDER
19 WHICH THE MANUFACTURER GRANTS TO THE PERSON A LICENSE TO USE A TRADE
20 NAME, A SERVICE MARK, OR ANY OTHER PROPRIETARY IDENTIFIER; OR
21 (II) AUTHORIZATION UNDER ANOTHER ARRANGEMENT TO ACT
22 ON BEHALF OF THE MANUFACTURER.
23 (2) “AUTHORIZED REPAIR PROVIDER” INCLUDES A MANUFACTURER
24 WHEN THE MANUFACTURER:
25 (I) OFFERS TO PROVIDE SERVICES TO AN OWNER OF THE
26 MANUFACTURER’S EQUIPMENT REGARDING THE OWNER’S EQUIPMENT OR PART;
27 AND
28 (II) DOES NOT HAVE ANY ARRANGEMENT DESCRIBED IN

HOUSE BILL 31 3
1 PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION WITH AN UNAFFILIATED PERSON.
2 (C) “DOCUMENTATION” MEANS ANY MANUAL, DIAGRAM, REPORTING
3 OUTPUT, SERVICE CODE DESCRIPTION, SCHEMATIC, OR OTHER INFORMATION,
4 WHETHER IN ELECTRONIC OR TANGIBLE FORMAT, THAT A MANUFACTURER
5 PROVIDES TO AN AUTHORIZED REPAIR PROVIDER FOR THE PURPOSE OF ASSISTING
6 THE AUTHORIZED REPAIR PROVIDER WITH SERVICES PERFORMED ON THE
7 MANUFACTURER’S EQUIPMENT OR PART.
8 (D) (1) “EMBEDDED SOFTWARE” MEANS PROGRAMMABLE
9 INSTRUCTIONS PROVIDED ON FIRMWARE DELIVERED WITH AN ELECTRONIC
10 COMPONENT OF EQUIPMENT OR A PART TO RESTORE OR IMPROVE OPERATION OF
11 THE EQUIPMENT OR PART.
12 (2) “EMBEDDED SOFTWARE” INCLUDES ALL RELEVANT PATCHES
13 AND FIXES THAT THE MANUFACTURER MAKES TO EQUIPMENT OR A PART TO
14 RESTORE OR IMPROVE THE EQUIPMENT OR PART.
15 (E) “EQUIPMENT” MEANS A POWERED WHEELCHAIR.
16 (F) “FAIR AND REASONABLE TERMS AND COSTS” MEANS:
17 (1) WITH RESPECT TO OBTAINING FROM A MANUFACTURER ANY
18 DOCUMENTATION, PARTS, EMBEDDED SOFTWARE, FIRMWARE, OR TOOLS IN ORDER
19 TO PROVIDE SERVICES:
20 (I) TERMS THAT ARE EQUIVALENT TO THE MOST FAVORABLE
21 TERMS THE MANUFACTURER OFFERS TO AN AUTHORIZED REPAIR PROVIDER; AND
22 (II) COSTS THAT DO NOT EXCEED THE MANUFACTURER’S
23 SUGGESTED RETAIL PRICE, CALCULATED USING NET COSTS INCURRED AND
24 ACCOUNTING FOR ANY DISCOUNTS, REBATES, OR INCENTIVES OFFERED;
25 (2) WITH RESPECT TO OBTAINING FROM A MANUFACTURER ANY
26 DOCUMENTATION TO PROVIDE SERVICES, TERMS AND COSTS ON WHICH THE
27 MANUFACTURER AGREES TO PROVIDE THE DOCUMENTATION AND ANY RELEVANT
28 UPDATES AT NO CHARGE OTHER THAN, AT MOST, A CHARGE FOR THE
29 MANUFACTURER’S ACTUAL COSTS TO PREPARE AND SEND THE PRINTED COPY OF
30 THE DOCUMENTATION; AND
31 (3) WITH RESPECT TO OBTAINING FROM A MANUFACTURER TOOLS
32 THAT ARE SOFTWARE PROGRAMS, TERMS AND COSTS ON WHICH THE
33 MANUFACTURER AGREES TO PROVIDE THE TOOLS:

4 HOUSE BILL 31
1 (I) AT NO CHARGE AND WITHOUT REQUIRING AUTHORIZATION
2 OR INTERNET ACCESS, OR IMPOSING IMPEDIMENTS TO ACCESS OR USE THE TOOLS;
3 (II) DURING THE COURSE OF PERFORMING A DIAGNOSIS,
4 MAINTENANCE, OR A REPAIR AND IN A MANNER THAT ENABLES FULL
5 FUNCTIONALITY OF THE EQUIPMENT OR PART; AND
6 (III) IN A MANNER THAT DOES NOT IMPAIR THE EFFICIENT AND
7 COST–EFFECTIVE PERFORMANCE OF THE EQUIPMENT OR PART.
8 (G) “FIRMWARE” MEANS A SOFTWARE PROGRAM OR SET OF INSTRUCTIONS
9 PROGRAMMED ON EQUIPMENT OR A PART TO ALLOW THE EQUIPMENT OR PART TO
10 COMMUNICATE WITH ITSELF OR WITH OTHER COMPUTER HARDWARE.
11 (H) (1) “INDEPENDENT REPAIR PROVIDER” MEANS A PERSON IN THE
12 STATE THAT IS:
13 (I) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN PARAGRAPH (2)(I) OF THIS
14 SUBSECTION, NEITHER A MANUFACTURER’S AUTHORIZED REPAIR PROVIDER NOR
15 AFFILIATED WITH A MANUFACTURER’S AUTHORIZED REPAIR PROVIDER; AND
16 (II) ENGAGED IN OFFERING OR PROVIDING SERVICES.
17 (2) “INDEPENDENT REPAIR PROVIDER” INCLUDES:
18 (I) AN AUTHORIZED REPAIR PROVIDER IF THE AUTHORIZED
19 REPAIR PROVIDER IS OFFERING OR PROVIDING SERVICES FOR A DIFFERENT
20 MANUFACTURER OTHER THAN THE MANUFACTURER WITH WHOM THE AUTHORIZED
21 REPAIR PROVIDER HAS AN ARRANGEMENT AS DESCRIBED SUBSECTION (B)(1) OF
22 THIS SECTION; AND
23 (II) A MANUFACTURER THAT OFFERS OR PROVIDES SERVICES
24 FOR ANOTHER MANUFACTURER’S EQUIPMENT OR PART.
25 (I) “MANUFACTURER” MEANS A PERSON DOING BUSINESS IN THE STATE
26 AND ENGAGED IN THE BUSINESS OF SELLING, LEASING, OR SUPPLYING NEW
27 EQUIPMENT OR PARTS MANUFACTURED BY OR ON BEHALF OF ITSELF TO ANY
28 INDIVIDUAL, BUSINESS, OR OTHER ENTITY.
29 (J) “OWNER” MEANS A PERSON THAT OWNS EQUIPMENT OR AN AGENT OF
30 THE OWNER.

HOUSE BILL 31 5
1 (K) “PART” MEANS A NEW OR USED REPLACEMENT COMPONENT FOR
2 EQUIPMENT THAT A MANUFACTURER OFFERS FOR SALE OR MAKES AVAILABLE FOR
3 THE PURPOSE OF PROVIDING SERVICES.
4 (L) “POWERED WHEELCHAIR” MEANS A MOTORIZED WHEELED DEVICE
5 DESIGNED FOR USE BY A PERSON WITH A PHYSICAL DISABILITY.
6 (M) “SERVICES” MEANS DIAGNOSTICS, MAINTENANCE, OR REPAIRS
7 PERFORMED ON EQUIPMENT OR PARTS.
8 (N) (1) “TOOL” MEANS ANY SOFTWARE PROGRAM, HARDWARE
9 IMPLEMENT, OR OTHER APPARATUS USED FOR DIAGNOSIS, MAINTENANCE, OR
10 REPAIR OF EQUIPMENT OR PARTS.
11 (2) “TOOL” INCLUDES SOFTWARE OR OTHER MECHANISMS THAT
12 PROVIDE, PROGRAM, OR PAIR A NEW PART, CALIBRATE FUNCTIONALITY, OR
13 PERFORM ANY OTHER FUNCTION REQUIRED TO RETURN THE EQUIPMENT OR PART
14 TO FULLY FUNCTIONAL CONDITION.
15 (O) “TRADE SECRET” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 11–1201 OF THIS
16 ARTICLE.
17 14–5002.
18 (A) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION, TO
19 PROVIDE SERVICES FOR EQUIPMENT IN THE STATE, A MANUFACTURER SHALL, ON
20 FAIR AND REASONABLE TERMS AND COSTS, MAKE AVAILABLE TO AN INDEPENDENT
21 REPAIR PROVIDER OR OWNER OF THE MANUFACTURER’S EQUIPMENT ANY
22 DOCUMENTATION, PARTS, EMBEDDED SOFTWARE, FIRMWARE, OR TOOLS THAT ARE
23 INTENDED FOR USE WITH THE EQUIPMENT OR ANY PART, INCLUDING UPDATES TO
24 DOCUMENTATION, PARTS, EMBEDDED SOFTWARE, FIRMWARE, OR TOOLS.
25 (B) (1) FOR EQUIPMENT THAT CONTAINS AN ELECTRIC SECURITY LOCK
26 OR OTHER SECURITY–RELATED FUNCTIONS, A MANUFACTURER SHALL, ON FAIR AND
27 REASONABLE TERMS AND COSTS, MAKE AVAILABLE TO INDEPENDENT REPAIR
28 PROVIDERS ANY DOCUMENTATION, PARTS, EMBEDDED SOFTWARE, FIRMWARE, OR
29 TOOLS NEEDED TO RESET THE LOCK OR FUNCTION WHEN DISABLED IN THE COURSE
30 OF PROVIDING SERVICES.
31 (2) THE MANUFACTURER MAY MAKE THE DOCUMENTATION, PARTS,
32 EMBEDDED SOFTWARE, FIRMWARE, OR TOOLS AVAILABLE TO INDEPENDENT REPAIR
33 PROVIDERS AND OWNERS THROUGH APPROPRIATE SECURE RELEASE SYSTEMS.

