1 (C) (1) THE REQUIREMENTS OF SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION DO
2 NOT APPLY TO:
3 (I) A PART THAT IS NO LONGER AVAILABLE TO THE ORIGINAL
4 MANUFACTURER; AND
5 (II) CONDUCT THAT WOULD REQUIRE THE MANUFACTURER TO
6 DIVULGE A TRADE SECRET, UNLESS COMPLIANCE WITH SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS
7 SECTION IS NECESSARY TO PROVIDE SERVICES ON THE GROUNDS THAT THE
8 DOCUMENTATION, PART, EMBEDDED SOFTWARE, FIRMWARE, OR TOOL IS ITSELF A
9 TRADE SECRET.
10 (2) A MANUFACTURER MAY MAKE REDACTIONS TO REMOVE TRADE
11 SECRETS FROM THE DOCUMENTATION BEFORE PROVIDING THE DOCUMENTATION
12 IF THE USABILITY OF THE REDACTED DOCUMENTATION IS NOT DIMINISHED FOR
13 PURPOSES OF PROVIDING SERVICES.
14 (D) A MANUFACTURER IS NOT LIABLE FOR FAULTY OR IMPROPER REPAIRS
15 PROVIDED BY INDEPENDENT REPAIR PROVIDERS OR OWNERS, INCLUDING FAULTY
16 OR IMPROPER REPAIRS THAT CAUSE:
17 (1) DAMAGE TO EQUIPMENT THAT OCCURS DURING THE REPAIRS;
18 (2) ANY DIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, OR CONSEQUENTIAL
19 DAMAGES; OR
20 (3) AN INABILITY TO USE, OR A REDUCED FUNCTIONALITY OF,
21 EQUIPMENT THAT RESULTS FROM THE FAULTY OR IMPROPER REPAIR.
22 14–5003.
23 (A) NOTHING IN THIS SUBTITLE MAY BE CONSTRUED TO:
24 (1) LIMIT THE LIABILITY OF A PERSON UNDER A PRODUCTS LIABILITY
25 CLAIM; OR
26 (2) REQUIRE A MANUFACTURER TO PROVIDE AN INDEPENDENT
27 REPAIR PROVIDER OR OWNER ACCESS TO INFORMATION, OTHER THAN
28 DOCUMENTATION NECESSARY FOR COMPLIANCE WITH THIS SUBTITLE, THAT THE
29 MANUFACTURER PROVIDES TO AN AUTHORIZED REPAIR PROVIDER UNDER A
30 CONTRACT OR OTHER ARRANGEMENT.
31 (B) THE REQUIREMENTS AND REMEDIES PROVIDED UNDER THIS SUBTITLE

