1 MAY NOT BE WAIVED OR LIMITED BY A CONTRACT OR OTHER ARRANGEMENT.
2 14–5004.
3 A VIOLATION OF THIS SUBTITLE IS:
4 (1) AN UNFAIR, ABUSIVE, OR DECEPTIVE TRADE PRACTICE WITHIN
5 THE MEANING OF TITLE 13 OF THIS ARTICLE; AND
6 (2) SUBJECT TO THE ENFORCEMENT AND PENALTY PROVISIONS
7 CONTAINED IN TITLE 13 OF THIS ARTICLE.
8 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall be construed to
9 apply only prospectively and may not be applied or interpreted to have any effect on or
10 application to any contract that is executed between an authorized repair provider and a
11 manufacturer, as those terms are defined in § 14–5001 of the Commercial Law Article, as
12 enacted by Section 1 of this Act, before the effective date of this Act.
13 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
14 October 1, 2025.

